          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 24679,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "The Directive on Unfair Commercial Practices and the Directive on Unfair Terms in Consumer Contracts, as well as the Digital Services Act, serves EU consumers well in providing clear general rules and principles of consumer protection. Misguiding consumers online, hiding information on prices or contract terms, as well as confusing or misleading consumers when they are trying to exercise their rights or aggressive marketing practices when consumers are about to enter into an agreement is already forbidden.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s2",
          "section_path": [
            "Dark patterns, reactive design and issues with digital contracts."
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
