        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 15257,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "There is also national legislation enforcing good marketing practices, such as the Swedish concept of good credit practice \"god kreditgivningssed\", where dark patterns, reactive design, and contractual issues such as the ones mentioned in the consultation does not belong. Detailed information requirements for financial products such as mortgages, other consumer credits, investment products, payment accounts and payment services also prevent such market practices. Some examples of dark patterns in the consultation, such as sneaking products into baskets, would also conflict with most, if not all, general contract law in member states.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s2",
          "section_path": [
