          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 8202,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Offers where prices are depending on conditions connected to the individual consumer are widely used to the benefit of consumers. Such offers should not lead to disadvantages or problems for consumers, provided that GDPR is followed. An example of personalised pricing is when a certain membership, such as a union membership, leads to reduced interest rates on a credit.",
