            "topic": "Unfair Pricing",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "The practice of connecting the price of a financial product to the risk associated with that product is not an unfair market practice."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 9426,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Financial products are due to their nature generally priced in accordance with a risk evaluation, where the risk often depends on circumstances connected to the consumer. The ability to assess and price risk is essential to financial institutions, and pricing risk is integral to how financial institutions function. The practice of connecting the price of a financial product to the risk associated with that product is not an unfair market practice. Regulations on marketing of prices limiting the possibility to price a financial product according to relevant risk in accordance with current legislation should not be introduced.",
